title: Sub-optimal codegenration for `match` expressions

labels.name: A-LLVM
labels.description: Area: Code generation parts specific to LLVM. Both correctness bugs and optimization-related issues.

labels.name: I-slow
labels.description: Problems and improvements with respect to performance of generated code.

labels.name: C-enhancement
labels.description: Category: An issue proposing an enhancement or a PR with one.

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:

As you can see `rustc` generated jumptable for the given example which is not something that should be. I'm expecting here to see a switch table, which is more efficient and desired for the mentioned code. Since rustc just delegates this to LLVM, the desicion on what to generate is done inside of it IIRC, I'll assume that during the IR generation rustc ends up with strange LLVM IR, and LLVM decides to use here Jump table over switch table for whatever reason.
